between these spatially inhomogeneous\nfields and matter configures a promising way to new avenues of research and\napplications. Thanks to the maturity that attosecond physics has reached,\ntogether with the tremendous advance in material engineering and manipulation\ntechniques, the age of atto-nano physics has begun, but it is in the initial\nstage. We present thus some of the open questions, challenges and prospects for\nexperimental confirmation of theoretical predictions, as well as experiments\naimed at characterizing the induced fields and the unique electron dynamics\ninitiated by them with high temporal and spatial resolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Jul 2016 05:09:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-29"}
